==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Miniate
<hw>Min"i*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Miniated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Miniating</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>miniatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>miniare</ets>. See
<er>Minium</er>.]</ety> <def>To paint or tinge with red lead or
vermilion; also, to decorate with letters, or the like, painted red, as
the page of a manuscript.</def> <rj><au>T. Wharton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Miniate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Miniate
<hw>Min"i*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
the color of red lead or vermilion; painted with vermilion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Miniature</ent>⟦br⟧
